dcterms:description: Publicly available recordings from mouse primary visual cortex (V1) containing neural responses to a natural movie stimulus, specifically a 30-second clip from 'Touch of Evil'. The dataset includes Neuropixels recordings from multiple animals, allowing for the study of representational drift in neural encoding.
dcterms:title: Allen Brain Observatory - Neuropixels Visual Coding

dcterms:creator: T. Comito
dcterms:description: A natural movie used as a stimulus in the study, specifically a 30-second clip from the film 'Touch of Evil'. This movie serves as a visual stimulus for analyzing neural responses in the primary visual cortex.
dcterms:title: Natural Movie 'Touch of Evil'
